{"questionId":"13432602","questionHtml":"<p>Find the linear regression equation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>, in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math>. Give the values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> to three decimal places.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>600</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>908</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>600</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>908</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Long answer for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>599991</mn><mo>…</mo></math> and for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>90772</mn><mo>…</mo></math> If both answers are correct but not given to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> decimal places award <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13432602","referenceCode":"23N.1.AHL.TZ0.10b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the linear regress